 East London - The Buffalo City Metro Executive Mayor, Xola Pakati, turned the sod in Mdantsane, East London, to mark the start of Mdantsane internal road construction on Tuesday. This marked the beginning of construction for phase 4A Mdantsane internal roads. Works on the main road, the Qumza Highway, are also still ongoing. Speaking at the construction site, Pakati said: "We are here in Mdantsane to introduce the contractors for the Phase 4A Mdantsane internal road construction from gravel to tarred. "The people of Mdantsane have been witnessing us working hard changing the face of this township by fixing the infrastructure." The project is scheduled for completion by the end of 2021. The R14 million project will done in clusters covering the following wards: Cluster 1 includes Ward 11,12,17,14 & 42, Cluster 2 includes Ward 17,20,30 & 48, Cluster 3 Ward 24. The Executive Mayor conitued and said: “This part of the on going work done by the City to deliver services to the people as well as improve the infrastructure in our township." "This is the task we are determined that we will complete before end of the term in office," said Pakati. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  